Premaxilla with outer series of small conical teeth and inner band of much smaller teeth; anteriorly, teeth in outer series considerably enlarged; premaxillary notch toothless. Dentary with band of small conical teeth extending from elevated posterodorsal surface of jaw almost to symphysis; numerous teeth at anterior end of jaw adjacent to symphysis and on elevated posterodorsal surface of jaw conspicuously enlarged; many of enlarged teeth at anterior end of jaw exserted and fitting into premaxillary notch when mouth closed; symphysis toothless. Vomer and palatine with teeth; vomerine tooth patch small, chevron shaped or quadrangular, without posterior prolongation; palatine teeth in longitudinal band. Endopterygoid usually with teeth. Tongue with or without teeth. Four of the five specimens examined are males; they have the dentition much better developed than does the single female (see
Fig. 2
).
